{
  "texts": [
    "The target data W s rep- resents the training set, L s represents the two-class labeling (deepfake, non-deepfake), and D s depicts the classifier to be produced.",
    "As defined,D = {G s, L s, S s }.",
    "The classifier to be built could be described as S s ( G s, L s |T) in TL.",
    "The classifier is described as D s ( G s, L s) without utilizing TL [25].So we may conclude that D s (G s, L s |T) is predicted to be a considerably nearer classifier S ideal 2 than the classifier that utilizes just the target domain D s G s, L s, assum- ing a significant number of samples W and labels L. Thus,err[S s G s, L s | | T)(G), L] < err[D s (G s, L s)(G), L].The error function err(a, b) computes the difference between the two inputs, a and b.",
    "Building and training a network from the start are one of the most important aspects that can help TL improve its efficacy."
  ]
}